The paper discusses a Python toolbox for sampling from determinantal point processes (DPPs), which are used in various fields including machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) as DPPs are also used in coding theory. The paper also mentions that DPPs are used as models and computational tools in physics, statistics, and probability, which suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) could also be relevant sub-categories. Finally, since the paper discusses sampling algorithms, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) could also be a possible sub-category.
